      • IndexDirectoryOnDisk

        public IndexDirectoryOnDisk​(String name,
                            IndexFunction<T> indexFunction,
                            Formatter<T> indexFormatter)
        Constructs a IndexDirectoryOnDisk instance that represents a directory, containing an index in the form of sub directories.
        Parameters:
        name - The name that this directory should have on disk.
        indexFunction - An IndexFunction that calculates the index of this IndexDirectoryOnDisk from a ImmutableStack of parent IndexDirectoryOnDisk indices. The top element of the stack is from the closest IndexDirectoryOnDisk in the parent chain.
        indexFormatter - A Formatter used to format the directory name for each index element returned by the indexFunction.
